      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "libsecp256k1 is not a multi-threaded library. If you want to make use of multiple cores, you need to invoke it from multiple threads yourself (the library is thread-safe, in that you can invoke it multiple times simultaneously, and even reuse the same context across threads if you only use functions that take constant contexts).\n\nBeyond, key generation is very much optimized, and uses significant precomputed table to reduce the number of operations. Generating a key takes far less than 256 point additions.",
